<div class='question-begin'>Optional Extra 2</div><div class='question-body'>


Using the data from the past surveys: [https://uoepsy.github.io/data/surveydata_historical.csv](https://uoepsy.github.io/data/surveydata_historical.csv).  

Is students' preference for evenings over mornings associated with a pet preference (cats vs dogs)? 



</div><p class="question-end"></p>




<div style="display:none;">






::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
surveydata <- read_csv("https://uoepsy.github.io/data/surveydata_historical.csv")

surveydata |> 
  select(ampm, catdog) |>
  table() |> print() |>
  chisq.test()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
                catdog
ampm             cat dog
  Evening person  56  72
  Morning person  33  37
```


:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```

	Pearson's Chi-squared test with Yates' continuity correction

data:  print(table(select(surveydata, ampm, catdog)))
X-squared = 0.09573, df = 1, p-value = 0.757
```


:::
:::






</div><p class="solution-end"></p>










